Warning: this is the smallest streamgroup I could find. Anything larger could be problematic on a Jupyter notebook.

[1]:

sample_file = r"streamgroups/det_city_tunnel1_tunel.drm"

from pyDXHR.cdcEngine.Archive import Archive
from pyDXHR.cdcEngine.DRM.DRMFile import DRM
from pyDXHR.cdcEngine.Sections import RenderMesh

pc_base = Archive()
pc_base.deserialize_from_file(r"C:\Users\vardo\DXHR_Research\DXHR\BIGFILE.000")

pc_base_raw_data = pc_base.get_from_filename(sample_file)
pc_base_drm = DRM()
pc_base_drm.deserialize(pc_base_raw_data)

pc_base_drm.Sections

[2]:

pc_rm = RenderMesh.deserialize_drm(pc_base_drm)

out_mesh = []
for mesh in pc_rm:
    out = mesh.to_gltf(as_bytes=True, blank_materials=True, apply_scale=True)
    out_mesh.append(out)

[6]:

import trimesh
from io import BytesIO

data = [trimesh.load(BytesIO(m), file_type="glb") for m in out_mesh]
scene = trimesh.Scene(data)
scene.show(flags={'axis': True})
